From the Experimental Results As Well As the Average
Kinetic Energy,Mean Momentum and Cascade Deposition
The Recoil Properties of Some Nuclides were Determined.
The Thick Target and Thick Catcher Method Combined with
Determine the Cross Sections and Recoil Properties of
Some Nuclides Which have Been Produced in the
Bombardment of Gold with 580 MeV Protons. The Mass
Range in the Investigation was 46<=a<=110 Most Nuclides
Having Mass Numbers Between 83 and 96. The Charge
Dispersion Curve and the Mass-Yield-Curve For this
Latter Mass Range have Been Calculated from the
Experimental Results As Well As the Average Kinetic
Energy, Mean Momentum, and Cascade Deposition Energy
For Each Observed Product. These Data Show a Good
Qualitative and Quantitative Agreement with Values
Which are Characteristic For Fission Products. It is
Therefore Concluded That Products of Mean Masses are
Produced at 580 MeV Proton Energy from Gold Mainly by
